      "repair_reason": "- [P1] Human review is needed because the remaining blockers are contributor real behavior proof and maintainer cap acceptance, not a narrow code repair ClawSweeper can safely perform.; Cleared: The diff narrows an existing network buffering path with an existing internal bounded reader and adds no dependencies, workflow permissions, secrets handling, lifecycle hooks, or package-resolution changes. (sha=91b744e500f8e8151ba3130a867c296de04ad2e5)",
      "review_summary": "The PR bounds tools-manager GitHub latest-release JSON reads with `readResponseWithLimit`, exports `getLatestVersion` for tests, and adds a focused proof test file.\n\nPR surface: Source +6, Tests +62. Total +68 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. Current main and `v2026.6.10` both read the tools-manager GitHub latest-release success body through `response.json()`, so the unbounded path is source-reproducible without forcing an OOM scenario.",
      "review_followup": "- [P1] Human review is needed because the remaining blockers are contributor real behavior proof and maintainer cap acceptance, not a narrow code repair ClawSweeper can safely perform.",
      "freeform_prompt": null,
      "visual_lens": null,
